                <h2>Our Story</h2>
                <p>
                    We are a team of passionate graduate students from the Master of Science in Computer Science program
                    at Stevens Institute of Technology. Our journey began in a classroom where we shared a common
                    concern about food waste and its impact on our environment and communities. Inspired to make a
                    difference, we conceptualized ZeroWaste â€“ a Food Waste Management Application, born out of our
                    collective ambition to leverage technology for a sustainable future.
                </p>
                <p>
                    ZeroWaste is more than just an app; it's a testament to our belief that technology can be a force
                    for good. From late-night coding sessions to brainstorming the user experience, every step in our
                    journey has been driven by our commitment to reducing food waste. We have poured our knowledge,
                    skills, and hearts into developing an app that not only addresses a critical environmental issue but
                    also empowers individuals and organizations to take meaningful action.
                </p>
            </section>

            <section>
                <h2>Our Mission</h2>
                <p>
                    At the heart of ZeroWaste lies our mission: to reduce food waste through innovative technology
                    solutions. We strive to create a world where every bit of food is valued and utilized to its fullest
                    potential. Our app is designed to assist users in efficiently managing food inventories, tracking
                    expiration dates, and facilitating the sharing and donation of food items.
                </p>
                <p>
                    We are committed to fostering responsible consumption habits and promoting a community-driven
                    approach to minimize food waste. Our mission extends beyond the app as we aim to educate and inspire
                    action towards sustainable food practices. By integrating features like composting guidance, recipe
                    suggestions, and rewards for efficient food use, we hope to cultivate a culture of mindfulness
                    around food usage and waste.
                </p>
            </section>

